# circleci_context_restriction (Resource)

Manages a restriction on a CircleCI context. Restrictions control which projects or groups can use a context.

## Example Usage

```terraform
resource "circleci_context_restriction" "example" {
  context_id = "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000"
  type       = "project"
  value      = "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001"
}
```

<!-- schema generated by tfplugindocs -->
## Schema

### Required

- `context_id` (String) The ID of the context to restrict.
- `type` (String) The type of restriction (e.g., `project`).
- `value` (String) The value associated with the restriction type (e.g., the project ID).

### Read-Only

- `id` (String) The unique identifier of the restriction.
- `name` (String) The name associated with the restriction.
- `project_id` (String) The project ID associated with the restriction.

## Import

Import is supported using `context_id/restriction_id`:

```shell
terraform import circleci_context_restriction.example "<context_id>/<restriction_id>"
```
